snippet.textDisplay:
"Some people let go
Some people let love slip away, yeah
But I'm gonna hold on
When no one believes, I'll keep the faith"

This stanze is him telling his significant other that he refuses to let the relationship end and that he still loves them. Everyone believes they split up and won't carry on but he's "keeping the faith"


"And I know that we're in trouble
But I swear that we'll survive"

He knows they really don't have a chance but he's going to try his damn best to make sure their relationship survives.


"If we were deep-sea divers
And no one came to find us
If you had nothing left
I'd give you my last breath (Oh-oh-oh, oh, oh)
I'd give you my last breath (Oh-oh-oh, oh, oh)"

He trying to show his devotion

"We all need a lifeline
Someone to call when we're alone, hmm, yeah
It's all good in the good times
But I'll still be there when it all goes wrong
Yes, I will"

From this verse it makes me believe his significant other is struggling from mental health issues and he's trying to tell her that we all need help if that's not him at least a mental health professional.
---------
TLDR
From the lyrics, it reminds me of a couple who are struggling as one is having mental health issues which are rupturing the relationship and other is calling out to them trying to get through to them that's they can work through this. But idk

snippet.textDisplay: I'm from the UK and i'm usually not a fan of our entries but this is a good song. What an improvement from last year! I really enjoy how modern it sounds. The BBC really took the hint and has sent something the artist had some involvement in making. Having a song the artist is emotionally invested in really adds to the story and ability for the audience to connect with it.
